# TYPESCRIPT/JAVASCRIPT PATTERNS

## API Response Format
```typescript
interface ApiResponse<T> {
  success: boolean
  data?: T
  error?: string
  meta?: { total: number; page: number; limit: number }
}
```

## Custom Hooks Pattern
```typescript
export function useDebounce<T>(value: T, delay: number): T {
  const [debouncedValue, setDebouncedValue] = useState<T>(value)
  useEffect(() => {
    const handler = setTimeout(() => setDebouncedValue(value), delay)
    return () => clearTimeout(handler)
  }, [value, delay])
  return debouncedValue
}
```

## Immutable Updates
```typescript
// WRONG
function updateUser(user, name) {
  user.name = name
  return user
}

// CORRECT
function updateUser(user, name) {
  return { ...user, name }
}
```

---

# YOURDOMI-SPECIFIC PATTERNS

## Currency & Numbers
- All currency is EUR
- Format: `new Intl.NumberFormat('nl-BE', { style: 'currency', currency: 'EUR' }).format(amount)`
- Occupancy rates: stored as decimals (0.72), displayed as percentages (72%)
- Never display raw API numbers — always run through formatter functions

## Property Analysis
- Deal scores are 0–100; display with color coding (red <40, amber 40-70, green >70)
- Owner earnings projections must show monthly AND annual breakdowns
- Permit/compliance content is city-specific — always check `city` prop before rendering

## Lead Capture
- Lead modal must always have a visible close mechanism
- Form validation runs on submit, not on every keystroke
- On successful submission, show confirmation before redirecting

## Styling (Tailwind)
- Use Tailwind utility classes; avoid inline styles except for truly dynamic values
- Define brand colors in tailwind.config — don't hardcode hex values
- Use cn() utility (clsx/tailwind-merge) for conditional class names
- Mobile-first with md: and lg: breakpoints

---

# WHAT NOT TO DO
- Don't use console.log in committed code
- Don't add dependencies without checking bundle size impact
- Don't create files over 800 lines — split them
- Don't use `any` TypeScript type
- Don't use `// @ts-ignore`
- Don't leave TODO comments without a linked issue
- Don't fetch data directly in components — use hooks or query functions
- Don't mutate state directly — always use setState with new object references
